cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks related to face attribute classification. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep learning architecture for this task, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multi-net learning and model compression, which could fall under the sub-categories cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's use of neural networks for classification suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
